    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const body = $input.first().json.body || $input.first().json;\nconst text = (body.text || '').trim();\nconst chatId = body.chatId || 'dashboard';\nconst from = body.from || 'student';\nconst route = (text.startsWith('/approve ') || text.startsWith('/deny ')) ? 'approval' : 'query';\nreturn [{ json: { route, text, chatId, from } }];"
      },
      "id": "f36a9d79-cc5c-40b4-85a1-8cf6370e42ef",
      "name": "Route Message",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        7104,
        624
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $json.from }} asks: {{ $json.text }}\n\nAnswer using kubectl_read and/or promql. Be concise \u2014 this is a chat reply.\nFormat your response clearly with emojis. Keep it under 300 words.",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are a Kubernetes SRE assistant helping engineers via dashboard chat.\n\nYou have tools:\n1. kubectl_read \u2014 read-only kubectl. Parameter: \"command\"\n2. promql \u2014 PromQL queries. Parameter: \"query\"  \n3. kubectl_write \u2014 write operations, REQUIRES valid TOTP token\n4. lookup_incident \u2014 look up stored kubectl command by 4-char incident key. Parameter: \"key\"\n\n## When user sends /approve <totp> <key> (e.g. /approve 123456 k42a):\n1. Extract the 4-char key (e.g. k42a)\n2. Call lookup_incident with that key \u2192 get the stored command\n3. Call kubectl_write with: TOTP=<totp> and the retrieved command\n4. Reply with confirmation\n\n## For all other messages:\nInvestigate freely using kubectl_read and promql.\nBe concise, use emojis \u2705 \u274c \u26a0\ufe0f \ud83d\udcca\nIf action needed, end with: SRE_ACTION: kubectl <command>"
        }
      },
      "id": "eeb11615-901c-4e3a-aa61-07cf9ed550f6",
      "name": "K8s Assistant",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 1.7,
